# Cached artifacts produced by the eval pipeline.
# These regenerate from proforma.pdf + the live Brave/Gemini/Claude APIs
# whenever they're missing — committing them would create churn and bloat.
#
# Keep checked in:
#   - source files (tests/test_*.py, conftest.py, lib/judge*.py, tools/*.py)
#   - fixture inputs (proforma.pdf, metadata.json)
#   - documentation (README.md, docs/*.md, results/*.md)
#
# Ignore the derived caches and reports:

# Per-fixture caches (now under data/)
data/fixtures/*/web_context.txt
data/fixtures/*/pis_data*.json
data/fixtures/*/judge_*_cache.json

data/adversarial/*/web_context.txt
data/adversarial/*/pis_data*.json
data/adversarial/*/judge_*_cache.json
data/adversarial/*/layer5_verdict.json

# Timestamped run reports (now under results/runs/)
results/runs/*.json

# Working pytest logs from refresh runs — the curated copies under
# results/v*/pytest_full_output.log stay committed.
v*_pytest_output.log
v*_refresh_output.log

# Python bytecode
__pycache__/
*.pyc
